In article 2i8r8eEdiq@uni-erlangen.de, unrza3@cd4680fs.rrze.uni-erlangen.de (Markus Kuhn) writes:
> I'm interested in any information (especially references) about a
> cryptographic algorithm known as "Flat-Shamir" (might also be
> "Fiat-Shamir", it's a little bit unreadable). This algorithm
> is said to be used in the Videocrypt pay-TV encoding system.
> I'd also be interested in references about cryptoanalysis of 
> this algorithm. I've checked some of the usual crypto textbooks,
> but so far I didn't find any hints at all. Thanks for any info!

Try out "Security for Computer Networks" by D.W. Davies and W.L. Price,
2nd ed., 1989. It has some basics on Fiat-(like the italian car!! :-) ) 
Shamir protocols.

Or have a look at the original. A. Fiat, A. Shamir: 
How to Prove Yourself:  Practical Solutions to Identification 
and Signature Problems, in the Proc. of CRYPTO '86, 
Springer Lecture Notes on Computer Science 263, pp. 186-194, 1987.
I'm sure your library will have this.

Jochen.

